HJR316 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3
4 ENCOURAGING THE GOVERNOR TO PROMOTE THE TEXTILE RECYCLING
5 INDUSTRY IN ALABAMA.
6
7 WHEREAS, across the country, states, including
8 California, are moving to mandate end-of-life textile
9 collection and recycling; and
10 WHEREAS, these textile recycling laws are out of
11 touch and unduly burdensome, and businesses will surely look
12 to operate in more pro-business states; and
13 WHEREAS, Alabama has a centuries-old history in
14 producing high-quality cotton and textiles and is known for
15 its extremely business-friendly environment; and
16 WHEREAS, Alabama is uniquely suited to capitalize on
17 this market and become the epicenter of the textile
18 recycling industry in the United States; now therefore,
19 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
20 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That the Legislature encourages
21 the Governor and the relevant executive agencies to create a
22 plan to promote the textile recycling industry in the State
23 of Alabama.
